[{"type":"{{","value":[["pagebanner"],["Pagebanner default.jpg"]]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Image:Biysk-Railroad-Station.jpg"],["thumb"],["250px"],["Biysk Railway Station"]]},"\n",{"type":"'''","value":["Biysk"]}," (Бийск) is  the second largest city in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Altai Krai"]]}," with population of 220,000 people and featured as ",{"type":"''","value":["naukograd"]}," i.e. science city.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Understand"]},"\nBiysk is a starting point for tourists trekking to the Altay Mountains, 'the gateway to Mountainous Altai'.\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["Geography"]},"\nBiysk is located 163 km south of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Barnaul"]]}," and 356 km away from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Novosibirsk"]]},". The Mongolian border is farther 617 km south. The terrain around is a hilly plain. Separated by the river Biya both banks of the city are connected by three bridges. The city is situated on the Chuysky Highway, a tarmac road, which goes from Novosibirsk to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Mongolia"]]},".\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["History"]},"\nThe city appeared in 1709 as a part of the 'Biyskaya krepost', fortification line built from Ust'-Kamenogorsk. It derives the name from hydronym 'bi', a Samodian word for 'water, river'.\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["Climate"]},"\nContinental climate. The average temperature of January is -18C, in July it is +18,9C.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get in"]},"\nThere are no flights to Biysk airport so far because of reconstruction (03\/2011).\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By train"]},"\nThe direct trains are coming from Novosibirsk, Moscow, ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Tomsk"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Chita"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Omsk"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Surgut"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Krasnoyarsk"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Novokuznetsk"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Kemerovo"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Alma-Ata"]]},". Barnaul is the most probable place to arrive from.\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By bus"]},"\nBus station is serving routes from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Tomsk"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Belokurikha"]]},", Kemerovo, Novokuznetsk and Barnaul. Tickets are available via the internet. The bus station is  within 5 min walk from the railway station.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get around"]},"\nThe tram network is present with 8 routes. Public buses and taxis are numerous.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["See"]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Image:Uspensky temple in Biysk.jpg"],["thumb"],["250px"],["Assumption Temple"]]},"\nHistoric part of the city is the most curious place to give a look to where the architecture tells about the past epoch. Go on to the right bank of the river to enjoy 1900th houses of merchants, Passages and an Orthodox Temple, all in compact area.\n\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["listing"],["name=Museum of regional studies"],["url="],["email="],["address=134, Lenina st"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours=10:00-17:00 We-Su"],["price="],["content=Archeological artefacts from paleolith era. Numismatic and mineral collections. Mammoth cranium. Chinese pottery. The museum's co-founder was Vitaly Bianki ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Vitaly_Bianki"]}," whose memory is honoured in the museum's name. The museum's expositions are accommodated in two old buildings"]]}]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["listing"],["name=Museum of Chuysky Highway"],["url="],["email="],["address=10, Tsentralny pereoulok"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours=10:00-17:00 Mo-Fr"],["price="],["content=Museum's location is the left bank and rather far off from the city's center. This is the only museum in Russia dedicated to the history of road."]]}]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":["Your collection of Lenin's statues would be incomplete if you haven't taken a picture of one from Biysk. Thanks to cold weather Lenin was put a hat on here."]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":["There is a monument to the city's founder Peter the Great on the horseback. "]},{"type":"*","value":["If the weather permits one can see rockets being launched from the Baikonur cosmodrome, Kazakhstan. At nights rockets remind of comets."]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Do"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":["Visit the Drama theater."]},{"type":"*","value":["Go to the Bowling club."]},{"type":"*","value":["Musical theater ",{"type":"'''","value":["Echo"]},"."]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Buy"]},"\nTrade-center 'Maria-Ra' has a small souvenir shop inside.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Eat"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["eat"],["name=Bowling club"],["url="],["email="],["address=4, Chaikovskogo st"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone=+7 (3854) 34-70-07"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content="]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["eat"],["name=Grill house"],["url="],["email="],["address=59, Merlina st"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone=+7 (3854) 32-23-24"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content="]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["eat"],["name=Kalina Krasnaya"],["alt=Калина красная"],["url="],["email="],["address=164, Lva Tolstogo st"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone=+7 (3854) 33-77-92"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content="]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["eat"],["name=Praga"],["alt=Прага"],["url="],["email="],["address=65, Moprovsky pereoulok"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone=+7 (3854) 35-67-41, +7 (3854) 35-62-35"],["tollfree="],["fax=+7 (3854) 35-65-68"],["hours="],["price="],["content="]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Drink"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Sleep"]},"\n\nBusiness class\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["sleep"],["name=Hotel Tsentralnaya"],["alt=Центральная"],["url=http:\/\/central-hote